EBRD Lends $150 Million to Buyers of Istanbul Ferry Company

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-09-27T09:53:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/ebrd-lends-150-million-to-buyers-of-istanbul-ferry-company.html
The European Bank for
Reconstruction and Development will provide $150 million in
financing to the new owners of Istanbul’s ferry network to help
improve catering and introduce demand-based ticketing.  The lending is to TASS Denizcilik & Ulastirma Hizmetleri
Turizm Sanayi & Ticaret AS, the group that took over control of
the ferry company in June, the bank said today in an e-mailed
statement.  The group led by Souter Investment LLP, owned by U.K.-based
 Stagecoach Group Plc (SGC)  founder Brian Souter, and Turkish builder
 Akfen Holding AS (AKFEN)  purchased the city’s ferry company for $861
million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Steve Bryant in Ankara at 
 sbryant5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Holland at 
 bholland1@bloomberg.net  